# Usage UI & Pricing Rules

## Pricing policy

**Source-of-truth mandate** — When updating pricing anywhere (Go `pricing.go`,
JS `PRICING` object, `usage.mdc`, tests), the model MUST:

1. **Check the live provider pricing page** before writing code.
2. If the live page shows a **different price** from what exists in code:
   update **everywhere**: Go map, JS object, tests, and this file.
3. If the live page **matches** the code, note "verified — no change" and proceed.

Exception: **Thaura AI** hardcodes its price (`$0.50/$2.00` per 1M tokens).
Thaura's marketing page (`thaura.ai/pricing`) shows consumer plans, not API
rates. The API platform page at `https://thaura.ai/api-platform` documents
per-token rates but the page structure may change. Thaura pricing is the
fallback case — check the API platform page if available, otherwise keep the
last known value and note the date.

| Provider | Pricing page URL |
| ---- | --- |
| DeepSeek | https://api-docs.deepseek.com/quick_start/pricing |
| Moonshot / Kimi (K3) | https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/pricing/chat-k3.md |
| Moonshot / Kimi (K2.6) | https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/pricing/chat-k26.md |
| Thaura AI | https://thaura.ai/api-platform |

**Locations that must stay in sync** when prices change:
1. `internal/usage/pricing.go` — Go maps (`moonshotPricing`, `deepseekPricing`, `thauraPricing`)
2. `internal/usageui/static/index.html` — JS `PRICING` object
3. `internal/usage/pricing_test.go` — test expected values
4. `.cursor/rules/usage.mdc` — this file (update `last-verified` date)

